# Context engineering (reference)

Load manually via `@90-context-engineering` or read `docs/cursor/CONTEXT_BUDGET.md`.

## Do

- Start from `docs/cursor/REPO_MAP.md` + task template in `docs/cursor/templates/`.
- Paste short summaries: debug report `public_id`, `request_id`, failed step, error class.
- Offload huge logs to artifacts; reference path or admin report id.
- Task-scoped file lists from `docs/cursor/TASK_SCOPES.md`.

## Do not

- Paste full pytest output, raw JSON payloads, or multi-hundred-line stack traces.
- Load all `docs/` or entire test suite context by default.
- Use broad `grep` across repo when TASK_SCOPES gives entry points.

## Debug report reference format

```
Report: DBG-XXXXXXXXXX (/admin/debug-reports/DBG-XXXXXXXXXX)
Screen: route | City: zelenogradsk | Request: cg_req_123
Summary: import stalled at collecting_places; scopes 0/3
Error: ReviewQueueJobLinkError (fixed) / psycopg UndefinedTable
```

Full payload: fetch from admin or DB — not in prompt.
